Package : LayoutEditor 
Author : Shilpa Lawande

This package implements a Layout Editor which can create a layout in the form of boxes and
supports operations such as alignment, resizing, moving, grouping and rivetting. 

This can be used to create a standalone layout editor by creating an appropriate front end.
The file TestEditor.java is an example of how the front end of the layout editor may look.
Makes use of the MenuMaker and ToolbarMaker classes in AwtUtil package. 

Other packages used by this package :
Standard Java Packages
AwtUtil - Utility package to create menus, toolbars and other ui items. 
gjt - Graphic Java Toolkit for image buttons etc
COM.objectspace.JGL - A library for standard data structures such 
		      as List, Set, Iterators etc.
